{"word":"ἀγάλλω","slug":"ἀγάλλω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀγάλλω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, mostly in <a href='S:present tense'>pres.</a> and <a href='S:imperfect tense'>imperf.</a>\n<p/><i>to make glorious, glorify, exalt</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> : <a href='S:especially'>esp.</a> <i>to pay honour to a god</i>, <el>ἀγ. τινὰ θυσίαισι</el> <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>; <i>to adorn, deck</i>, <el>γαμηλίους εὐνάς</el> <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>; <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to glory, take delight, exult in</i> a thing, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, attic; <a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/>"}]}